## 1.01 truffle vscode and remix

1. Install VSCode
- Download from https://code.visualstudio.com/

2. Open 1.01-truffle-vscode-remix with VSCode then open terminal

3. Install node, yarn and truffle
- Install nvm https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm
- Install nodejs using nvm
- Install yarn https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install
- To make sure that all workshop is the same as in the video, make sure to use node v16.13.1 (LTS)
$ node -v
v16.13.1

$ yarn global add truffle

4. Init truffle project
$ truffle init

5. Explain directory structure of truffle project
/contracts
/migrations
/test
truffle-config.js

6. Compile truffle project
$ truffle compile

7. Open remix
- https://remix.ethereum.org/

8. Create file in remix named Helloworld.sol and place content in Helloworld.sol in remix editor

9. Explain how to compile and deploy in remix